<p class="has-200-font-size" style="line-height:var(--wp--custom--line-height--body)"><?php esc_html_e( 'The cellar was built in 1930 and is called the Cathedral Cellar because of a comment made by a Dutch poet, Antonie Donkersloot. As he entered the cellar, he exclaimed that it was indeed a true cathedral of wine, referring to the high dome-shaped ceiling (covering pressed aluminium) and tinted windows. This cellar was renovated in 2005 to create a serious wine production environment which could still accommodate public access. The Cathedral Cellar has been the playground of some of South Africa’s legendary winemakers and industry stalwarts. Step into the cellar and journey with us as we share this beautiful space’s engraved legacy. Experience Cathedral Cellar!', 'kwv' ); ?></p>
